  "prompt": "What should I do if someone loves me a lot more than I love him?",
  "response": "Navigating a relationship where feelings are unequal can be challenging. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to understand your own emotions. Why do you feel less? Is it a lack of chemistry, differing life goals, or something else?\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: Honesty is key in any relationship. If you feel comfortable, have a candid conversation with the person about your feelings. Make sure to approach the topic with sensitivity.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If you feel overwhelmed by their affection, it\u2019s important to set clear boundaries. Let them know what you\u2019re comfortable with in the relationship.\n\n4. **Consider Their Feelings**: Be mindful of how they might react. Remember that they may feel hurt or confused, so approach the conversation with empathy.\n\n5. **Assess the Relationship**: Think about whether the relationship can be adjusted to make both of you happy. Is there potential for improvement, or do the feelings seem too far apart?\n\n6. **Decide on the Future**: Based on your conversation and reflections, decide whether you want to continue in the relationship as-is, try to deepen your connection, or if it\u2019s best to part ways.\n\n7. **Be Kind**: If you decide to end the relationship, do it kindly and respectfully. Acknowledge their feelings and the time you've spent together.\n\n8. **Seek Support**: If you're finding it especially difficult, consider talking to a friend or a professional for guidance on how to handle the situation.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s okay to prioritize your feelings and well-being in any relationship.",
